{
  "description": "Residue-level gold standard for benchmarking the Target Priority Score. Positives are well-established oncogenic driver residues (canonical UniProt numbering) drawn from OncoKB, the cancerhotspots.org publications (Chang et al. 2016, 2018), and Vogelstein et al. 2013. This is a HIGH-PRECISION, not high-recall, set: absence of a residue does not prove it is a passenger. The benchmark evaluates each gene over its RECURRENT hotspot residues only (the hard task: separate true drivers from residues that are merely recurrent), so positives = curated drivers among a gene's hotspots and negatives = the remaining hotspots.",
